#Taken from Jon Froelich Notebook
# Returns all csv filenames in the given directory
def find_csv_filenames( path_to_dir, suffix=".csv" ):
    filenames = os.listdir(path_to_dir)
    return [ filename for filename in filenames if filename.endswith( suffix ) ]

#os.getcwd()
#find_csv_filenames(os.getcwd(), suffix=".csv")

def find_activity_filenames(path_to_dir, prefix):
    filenames = os.listdir(path_to_dir)
    return [ filename for filename in filenames if filename.startswith( prefix ) ]

bowlingarray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Underhand Bowling_Ac")
shakearray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Shake_Ac")
midairzorroarray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Zorro Z_Ac")
midaircounterclockwisearray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Counter Clockwise O_Ac")
forehandarray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Forehand Tennis_Ac")
backhandarray = find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Backhand Tennis_Ac")
baseballarray = find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Baseball Throw_Ac")
atrestarray= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "At Rest_Ac")
clockwisearray= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Clockwise O_Ac")
customgesturearray= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Your Custom Gesture_Ac")
sarray=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair S_Ac")

bowlgy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Underhand Bowling_Gy")
shakegy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Shake_Gy")
zorrogy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Zorro Z_Gy")
counterclockwisegy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Counter Clockwise O_Gy")
forehandgy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Forehand Tennis_Gy")
backhandgy = find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Backhand Tennis_Gy")
baseballgy = find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Baseball Throw_Gy")
atrestgy= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "At Rest_Gy")
clockwisegy= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair Clockwise O_Gy")
customgy= find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Your Custom Gesture_Gy")
sgy=find_activity_filenames (os.getcwd(), "Midair S_Gy")

#Bowling Data Plot - Frequency
f, axes = matplotlib.pyplot.subplots(1, figsize=(10,5))
for i in range(0,10):
    #print (i)
    j = pandas.read_csv(bowlingarray[i], header=0)
    axes.psd(j[[' X']], label = "bowling" + str(i+1))
    i=i+1
axes.legend()
axes.set_title('Bowling Accel X')

#Bowling Data Plot Line Graph
f, axes = matplotlib.pyplot.subplots(1, figsize=(10,5))
for i in range(0,10):
    #print (i)
    j = pandas.read_csv(bowlingarray[i], header=0)
    axes.plot(j[[' X']], label = "bowling" + str(i+1))
    i=i+1
axes.legend()
axes.set_title('Bowling Accel X')
axes.set_ylabel('Accel X')
axes.set_xlabel('Number of Data Points Collected')

import math

arrays = [bowlingarray, shakearray, midairzorroarray, midaircounterclockwisearray, forehandarray, 
          backhandarray,baseballarray, atrestarray, clockwisearray,sarray]
In [67]:
def calc_magnitude(x):
    accelmag=math.sqrt(x[0]*x[0]+x[1]*x[1]+x[2]*x[2])
    gyromag=math.sqrt(x[3]*x[3]+x[4]*x[4]+x[5]*x[5])
    return accelmag+gyromag

#creating dictionary of gesturetrial to associated dataframe
gesturetrial=dict()
for x in arrays:
    for i in range(0,10):
        gesturetrialdf=pandas.read_csv(x[i], header=0)
        gesturetrialdf= gesturetrialdf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' CurrentTimeMs', ' SensorTimestampNano'])
        #get gyro data
        x[i]=x[i].replace('Accelerometer', 'Gyroscope')
        gesturetrialgyrodf=pandas.read_csv(x[i], header=0)
        gesturetrialgyrodf=gesturetrialgyrodf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' CurrentTimeMs', ' SensorTimestampNano'])
        #join gyro data to accel data
        gesturetrialdf=gesturetrialdf.join(gesturetrialgyrodf, lsuffix='_accel', rsuffix='_gyro')
        x[i]=x[i].replace('Gyroscope', 'Accelerometer')
        #calculate magnitude for both gyro and accel
        magnitude=gesturetrialdf.apply(calc_magnitude, axis=1)
        #set magnitude to gesturetrial key in dictionary
        gesturetrial[x[i]]=magnitude

#do the same thing for custom gesture with different range because only 5 trials total for that dataset
for i in range (0,5):
    customgesturedf=pandas.read_csv(customgesturearray[i], header=0)
    customgesturedf= customgesturedf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' CurrentTimeMs', ' SensorTimestampNano'])
    customgesturearray[i]= customgesturearray[i].replace('Accelerometer', 'Gyroscope')
    customgesturegyrodf=pandas.read_csv(customgesturearray[i], header=0)
    customgesturegyrodf= customgesturegyrodf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' CurrentTimeMs', ' SensorTimestampNano'])
    customgesturedf= customgesturedf.join(customgesturegyrodf, lsuffix='_accel', rsuffix='_gyro')
    customgesturearray[i]= customgesturearray[i].replace('Gyroscope', 'Accelerometer')
    custommagnitude=customgesturedf.apply(calc_magnitude, axis=1)
    gesturetrial[customgesturearray[i]]=custommagnitude

for key, value in gesturetrial.items():    
    if "Bowling" in key:
        a=len(gesturetrial.get(key))
        bowlinglabel=[]
        for j in range(0, a):
            bowlinglabel.append("bowling")

        gesturetrial[key]=pandas.concat([gesturetrial[key], bowlinglab], axis=1)
        if b==0:
            testdata.append(gesturetrial[key])
            b=b+1
        else:
            trainingdatabowling.append(gesturetrial[key])
            b=b+1

#for any gesture dataframe that doesn't have the max length, append values with 0 to match the max length dataframe
for ind, x in enumerate(array):
    a,b=x.shape
    if a<maxLength:
        for i in range (0,maxLength-a):
            x=x.append(pandas.Series([0]), ignore_index=True)
            i=i+1
            if i==maxLength-a:
                print(x.shape)
                array[ind]=x
    else:
        array[ind]=x

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

            i=i+1
            if i==maxLength-a:

        array[ind]=x

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

    a,b=x.shape
    if a<maxLength:
        for i in range (0,maxLength-a):
            x=x.append(pandas.Series([0]), ignore_index=True)
            i=i+1
            if i==maxLength-a:
                print(x.shape)
                array[ind]=x
    else:
        array[ind]=x

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

#lets pad these dataframes with zeros

maxLength=0
for ind, x in enumerate(array):
    a,b=x.shape
    print (a)
    if a>maxLength:
        maxLength=a
        #print (x)
        print ("maxLengthSet")
        print (a)

#for any gesture dataframe that doesn't have the max length, append values with 0 to match the max length dataframe
for ind, x in enumerate(array):
    a,b=x.shape
    if a<maxLength:
        for i in range (0,maxLength-a):
            x=x.append(pandas.Series([0]), ignore_index=True)
            i=i+1
            if i==maxLength-a:
                print(x.shape)
                array[ind]=x
    else:
        array[ind]=x

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

maxLength=0
for ind, x in enumerate(array):
    a,b=x.shape
    print (a)
    if a>maxLength:
        maxLength=a
        #print (x)
        print ("maxLengthSet")
        print (a)

#for any gesture dataframe that doesn't have the max length, append values with 0 to match the max length dataframe
for ind, x in enumerate(array):
    a,b=x.shape
    if a<maxLength:
        for i in range (0,maxLength-a):
            x=x.append(pandas.Series([0]), ignore_index=True)
            i=i+1
            if i==maxLength-a:
                print(x.shape)
                array[ind]=x
    else:
        array[ind]=x

#Running DTW classifier
from scipy.spatial.distance import euclidean
from fastdtw import fastdtw

#EXAMPLE
#distance, path = fastdtw(temparray[0][' X'], temparray[1][' X'], dist=euclidean)


testarray=[]
testarray.append(test_X.iat[0,0])
a, b = test_X.shape
results=numpy.empty((0,3), int)
c=len(array)
print ("Length of Gesture Array")
print (c)
print (a)
#dtw will compare one row of testdata with a full gesture dataframe -- e.g. the entire bowling dataframe
#and then store the dataframe with which it has the min distance according to fastdtw
#along with the min distance 
for i in range (0,a):
    temp=[]
    temp.append(test_X.iat[i,0])
    print ("Test Mag Trial")
    print (i)
    for j in range (0,c):
        gesturetest=array[j]
        distance,path = fastdtw(temp, gesturetest, dist=euclidean)
        if j == 0:
            mindistance=distance
            gestureclass=j
        else:
            if distance < mindistance:
                mindistance=distance
                gestureclass=j
    #gestureclass is the index of array which is what I use to determine the classification given (whatever it finds as mindistance)
    newrow=[i, gestureclass, mindistance]
    results=numpy.vstack([results, newrow])

#SVM Approach

import math
arrays = [bowlingarray, shakearray, midairzorroarray, midaircounterclockwisearray, forehandarray, 
          backhandarray,baseballarray, atrestarray, clockwisearray,sarray]
    #trying without gyroscope data for classification

In [42]:
#creating SVM dictionary with relevant features
def calc_magnitude_accel(x):
    return math.sqrt(x[1]*x[1]+x[2]*x[2]+x[3]*x[3])

def calc_magnitude_gyro(x):
    return math.sqrt(x[5]*x[5]+x[6]*x[6]+x[7]*x[7])

svmgesturetrial=dict()
for x in arrays:
    for i in range(0,10):
        svmgesturetrialdf=pandas.read_csv(x[i], header=0)
        svmgesturetrialdf= svmgesturetrialdf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' SensorTimestampNano'])
        #print (svmgesturetrialdf)
        x[i]=x[i].replace('Accelerometer', 'Gyroscope')
        #print (x[i])
        svmgesturetrialgyrodf=pandas.read_csv(x[i], header=0)
        svmgesturetrialgyrodf= svmgesturetrialgyrodf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' SensorTimestampNano'])
        svmgesturetrialdf=svmgesturetrialdf.join(svmgesturetrialgyrodf, lsuffix='_accel', rsuffix='_gyro')
        #print (svmgesturetrialdf)
        x[i]=x[i].replace('Gyroscope', 'Accelerometer')
        #print (x[i])
        a,b = svmgesturetrialdf.shape
        array=[]
        timeoftrial= svmgesturetrialdf.iat[a-1,0]-svmgesturetrialdf.iat[0,0]
        magnitudeaccel=svmgesturetrialdf.apply(calc_magnitude_accel, axis=1)
        meanmagnitudeaccel=magnitudeaccel.mean()
        meanxaccel=svmgesturetrialdf[' X_accel'].mean()
        meanyaccel=svmgesturetrialdf[' Y_accel'].mean()
        meanzaccel=svmgesturetrialdf[' Z_accel'].mean()
        
        magnitudegyro=svmgesturetrialdf.apply(calc_magnitude_gyro, axis=1)
        meanmagnitudegyro=magnitudegyro.mean()
        meanxgyro=svmgesturetrialdf[' X_gyro'].mean()
        meanygyro=svmgesturetrialdf[' Y_gyro'].mean()
        meanzgyro=svmgesturetrialdf[' Z_gyro'].mean()
        
        array = [timeoftrial, meanmagnitudeaccel, meanxaccel, meanyaccel, meanzaccel, meanmagnitudegyro, meanxgyro,meanygyro,  meanzgyro]
        svmgesturetrial[x[i]]=array
        

for i in range (0,5):
    customgesturedf=pandas.read_csv(customgesturearray[i], header=0)
    customgesturedf= customgesturedf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' SensorTimestampNano'])
    customgesturearray[i]=customgesturearray[i].replace('Accelerometer', 'Gyroscope')
    customgesturegyrodf=pandas.read_csv(x[i], header=0)
    customgesturegyrodf=customgesturegyrodf.drop(columns=['Sensor',' SensorTimestampNano'])
    customgesturedf=customgesturedf.join(customgesturegyrodf, lsuffix='_accel', rsuffix='_gyro')
    customgesturearray[i]=customgesturearray[i].replace('Gyroscope', 'Accelerometer')
    
    a, b = customgesturedf.shape
    timeoftrialcustom=customgesturedf.iat[a-1,0]-customgesturedf.iat[0,0]
    magnitudeaccel=customgesturedf.apply(calc_magnitude_accel, axis=1)
    meanmagnitudeaccel=magnitudeaccel.mean()
    meanxaccel=customgesturedf[' X_accel'].mean()
    meanyaccel=customgesturedf[' Y_accel'].mean()
    meanzaccel=customgesturedf[' Z_accel'].mean()
    
    magnitudegyro=customgesturedf.apply(calc_magnitude_gyro, axis=1)
    meanmagnitudegyro=magnitudegyro.mean()
    meanxgyro=customgesturedf[' X_gyro'].mean()
    meanygyro=customgesturedf[' Y_gyro'].mean()
    meanzgyro=customgesturedf[' Z_gyro'].mean()
    
    customarray=[timeoftrial, meanmagnitudeaccel, meanxaccel, meanyaccel, meanzaccel, meanmagnitudegyro, meanxgyro,meanygyro,  meanzgyro]
    svmgesturetrial[customgesturearray[i]]=customarray

    if "Shake" in key:
        if key==shakearray[4]:
            tempseries=pandas.Series(svmgesturetrial[key], index=['trialtime', 'meanmagaccel', 'meanxaccel', 'meanyaccel', 'meanzaccel', 'meanmaggyro', 'meanxgyro', 'meanygyro', 'meanzgyro', 'gesture'])
            testdatadf=testdatadf.append(tempseries, ignore_index=True)
            #sh=sh+1
        else:
            tempseries=pandas.Series(svmgesturetrial[key], index=['trialtime', 'meanmagaccel', 'meanxaccel', 'meanyaccel', 'meanzaccel', 'meanmaggyro', 'meanxgyro', 'meanygyro', 'meanzgyro', 'gesture'])
            trainingdatadf=trainingdatadf.append(tempseries, ignore_index=True)
            #sh=sh+1    
                                
    if "Your Custom" in key:
        if key==customgesturearray[4]:
            tempseries=pandas.Series(svmgesturetrial[key], index=['trialtime', 'meanmagaccel', 'meanxaccel', 'meanyaccel', 'meanzaccel', 'meanmaggyro', 'meanxgyro', 'meanygyro', 'meanzgyro', 'gesture'])
            testdatadf=testdatadf.append(tempseries, ignore_index=True)
            #cu=cu+1
        else:
            tempseries=pandas.Series(svmgesturetrial[key], index=['trialtime', 'meanmagaccel', 'meanxaccel', 'meanyaccel', 'meanzaccel', 'meanmaggyro', 'meanxgyro', 'meanygyro', 'meanzgyro', 'gesture'])
            trainingdatadf=trainingdatadf.append(tempseries, ignore_index=True)
            #cu=cu+1

#Create SVM - pulled from http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.svm.SVC.html
from sklearn.svm import SVC


model=SVC(kernel="rbf", C=100, gamma=.01)
model.fit(trainingdata_x, trainingdata_y)
results=model.predict(test_x)
